      <scopecontent id="aspace_057d74a3687f658b5323d5a4279abee6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of historic and modern bookplates either commissioned by Polish individuals and institutions or designed by Polish artists. The collection also includes related correspondence and ephemeral materials. Series IV includes documentation of former Bookplate Curator Warren Lowenhaupt's participation in the 1964 International Ex Libris Congress in Krakow, Poland.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_20059cc5c82067cbf19bbe261a92a5f4">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into four series: I. Bookplates – Historical, II. Bookplates – Artists, III. Bookplates – Individuals, IV. Bookplates – Personal Collections. Any correspondence or ephemeral materials relating to a specific bookplate are filed together with the bookplate.</p>  
      </arrangement>
